Disclaimer: I didn't actually take this course this semester, but I was in the other deep learning class (294-129) and I'm planning on taking 131 next semester, I also knew a number of people in 131 this semester.

My guess is that they would want you to have courses equivalent to 53/54, plus some knowledge of probability. Additionally I would be very surprised if 189 wasn't a prereq. I had to ask Professor Canny to take 129 this semester, and for undergraduates he really was looking for 53+110+127/126+188+189, but I think that was on the high end of requirements.

No idea about the P/NP thing. My guess is that they don't love it because they're already worried enough about undergrads not taking grad courses seriously, but I have no idea.

https://www2.eecs.berkeley.edu/Courses/Data/1174.html

What sort of background is required for this class? Can I P/NP classes like this as an undergraduate?
